1.npm init:
To initialize the npm package
2.Install Dependencies:
(i)npm install express body-parser mongoose concurrently- The express backend framework,body-parser
to retrieve the data that the users send via a body,mongoose for our db and concurrently to
run more than one npm script at a time so that we can run the server and the client at the same time.
(ii)npm install -D nodemon = Automatically reloads the server when we modify and save somrthing in our code and
we're saving it only for our Dev dependency.
(iii)We add the below codes in the scripts->package.json
"start": "node server.js",
"server": "nodemon server.js"
